National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with three top leaders of the Malaysian political opposition. They discussed the situation in Malaysia and their efforts to promote democracy, transparency, and reform. Rice emphasized the importance of upholding human rights, welcoming contributions from all citizens, and applying the rule of law fairly and apolitically. She expressed concerns about the prosecution and trial of opposition leader Mr. Anwar Ibrahim, highlighting the need for an independent judiciary. Rice also discussed the United States' commitment to political freedom, freedom of expression, freedom of association, and religious liberty, as well as the protection of rights regardless of ethnicity, gender, or sexual orientation. Finally, she offered condolences on the passing of democracy and civil rights activist Mr. Karpal Singh.